Package: pacifico
Type: Package
Title: Interface for the 'Pacifico' Python Library
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(person(given = c("Burrus", "Financial"),
                      family = "Intelligence",
                      role = "aut"),
               person(given = "Jacques",
                      family = "Burrus",
                      role = "cre",
                      email = "jacques.burrus@bfi.lat"))
Description: Provides an interface to the 'Pacifico' Python library, allowing users to request financial
    market data and convert date formats seamlessly between R and 'Python'. The package automates Python
    environment setup through 'reticulate' and simplifies the process of working with the 'Pacifico' API
    for economic research and analysis.
Depends: R (>= 4.0)
